Description: Handle sliver of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Probably drawn by Petrie (Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 200, 9). Name Olympos.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0887)
